b'Join the Celebration \xe2\x80\x93 Healthcare Simulation Week: September 17-21\n'
b'As leaders in health care delivery, translational research and education across multiple diverse disciplines, UI Health is committed to training the health care leaders of the future. One element of modern education for practitioners and students today is through medical simulation techniques.\xc2\xa0Learn More Here'
b'Learn More Here'
b'College of Medicine Graduation Shakes the UIC Pavilion\nThe cavernous UIC Pavilion might only have been half-filled with families and friends of the College of Medicine\xe2\x80\x99s 327 graduates for 2018, but the noise level as they filed across the stage on May 11 probably rivaled that of many a rock concert or hockey game.\xc2\xa0UIC Chancellor Michael Amiridis, PhD, invited those assembled to show loud enthusiasm for the graduates. \xe2\x80\x9cThis is your opportunity to show our graduates how proud you are,\xe2\x80\x9d he said. \xe2\x80\x9cThey deserve to have this building shaking as I say, \xe2\x80\x98Congratulations to the Class of 2018!\xe2\x80\x99 Thank you for everything you have done to support our students.\xe2\x80\x9d'
b'2018 College of Medicine at Chicago Faculty Recognition Ceremony\nThe 2018 College of Medicine at Chicago Faculty Recognition Ceremony was held on May 9, 2018 to honor this year\xe2\x80\x99s recipients of the Departmental Faculty of the Year and the Departmental Rising Star awards. There were over 100 in attendance, with 36 faculty receiving honors during this very special event. Click here to see pictures from the event.'
